  <article class="article-content">
    <h1 class="lang-content lang-zh active">OpenAI 推出 Workspace Agents 抢占团队协作入口</h1>
    <h1 class="lang-content lang-en">OpenAI launches workspace agents to own the team workflow layer</h1>
    
    <time datetime="2026-04-22">2026-04-22</time>
    
    <div class="lang-content lang-zh active">
      <p>OpenAI 推出 Workspace Agents，这一步的重点不是再做一个更会聊天的助手，而是把智能体正式推进到团队共享工作流里。相比个人使用的 GPTs，Workspace Agents 更像企业内部可复用的“工作节点”：它们能接工具、跑流程、记住上下文、在 Slack 和 ChatGPT 里持续处理任务。</p>
      
      <p>这件事之所以重要，是因为企业里的高价值工作很少是单人单轮完成的。它往往依赖共享知识、审批链路、跨团队协作和长期上下文。OpenAI 这次发布，本质上是在争夺企业软件栈里一个更上游的位置——不是回答问题，而是承接流程。</p>
      
      <p>从产品形态看，Workspace Agents 也让 OpenAI 的路线更清晰了。Codex 负责在云端执行，连接文件、代码、记忆和外部工具；Slack 负责进入协作场景；分析和权限控制则帮助它跨进企业采购的门槛。也就是说，OpenAI 不只是想提供一个模型接口，它想提供一套可共享、可治理、可部署的 agent 平台。</p>
      
      <p>更值得警惕的是，这会加剧企业协作入口的竞争。微软已经有 Copilot 和 Microsoft 365，Google 有 Workspace 生态，而 OpenAI 现在通过 ChatGPT 和 Slack 集成切入。谁能最先把“团队知识 + 工具调用 + 自动执行”做成默认体验，谁就更有可能成为组织里的 AI 操作层。</p>
      
      <p>研究预览期免费、随后转向 credit-based pricing，也说明这不是功能点试验，而是明确的商业产品路径。对 OpenAI 来说，Workspace Agents 不是 GPTs 的补充，而更像是其面向企业市场的第二阶段：从卖模型能力，走向卖持续运行的工作系统。</p>
      
      <p><a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-workspace-agents-in-chatgpt/" target="_blank">阅读原文</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="lang-content lang-en">
      <p>OpenAI’s workspace agents are not just a better assistant feature. They push agents into shared team workflows. Compared with personal GPTs, these agents look more like reusable work nodes inside an organization: they connect tools, follow processes, retain context, and keep operating across Slack and ChatGPT.</p>
      
      <p>That matters because high-value enterprise work is rarely completed by one person in one turn. It depends on shared knowledge, approvals, handoffs, and long-running context. This release is really OpenAI moving upstream in the enterprise stack. It is not just trying to answer questions. It is trying to absorb workflow.</p>
      
      <p>The product shape makes OpenAI’s strategy clearer. Codex handles cloud execution across files, code, memory, and tools. Slack integration gives it a collaboration surface. Analytics, permissions, and admin controls make it more compatible with enterprise buying requirements. In other words, OpenAI is no longer positioning itself as only a model provider. It is assembling a governed agent platform.</p>
      
      <p>This also intensifies the battle for the enterprise coordination layer. Microsoft already has Copilot and Microsoft 365. Google has Workspace. OpenAI is now entering through ChatGPT plus Slack. Whoever turns team knowledge, tool use, and autonomous execution into the default experience could become the operating layer for internal work.</p>
      
      <p>The pricing path is also telling. Free during research preview, then credit-based pricing, means this is not a side experiment. It is a product category OpenAI expects to monetize seriously. Workspace agents look less like an extension of GPTs and more like the next stage of OpenAI’s enterprise strategy: moving from selling model intelligence to selling persistent work systems.</p>
      
      <p><a href="https://openai.com/index/introducing-workspace-agents-in-chatgpt/" target="_blank">Read the full article</a></p>
    </div>
    
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to articles</a>
